10683, "(fr)IB Armorique - Torpedo Drone"
10684, "(fr)While provisionally classified as a bomber, the Armorique is often described as a 'torpedo drone'. At its front end, each drone mounts a standard ADEIS bomb, identical to the ones carried by Ys and Gradlon bombers. The rest of the drone acts as a booster stage to accelerate and guide the bomb into position. Unlike a standard torpedo, the Armorique carries a sophisticated onboard intelligence capable of intelligently selecting targets and approach vectors. While the Armorique's low cruising speed makes it easy to intercept, they typically deploy in swarms to overwhelm point defenses.<br/><br/>Much like the Ddraig, the Armorique typically functions as a weapon aboard A.D.E.IS.01. It seems to lack a subspace drive, and its ion drive is optimized for extreme range at the cost of a low top speed. Armoriques have also been observed to 'hibernate', allowing the class to function much like a mine. They possess minor stealth capabilities to assist in this role.<br/><br/>The Armorique's reliance on onboard intelligence prevents Locuste missiles from acquiring target lock, although Seldon receivers are still capable of detecting their presence. For this reason, they are considered a Class B threat."
10685, "(fr)IF Ddraig - Kamikaze Drone"
10686, "(fr)Preliminary classified as a fighter and named after the legendary 'Y Ddraig Goch' dragon of Welsh myth, the IF Ddraig is a light and highly maneuverable drone with an onboard disruption warhead. It was first encountered in the Doceitov Cloud deployed from A.D.E.IS.01.<br/><br/>While the Ddraig shares some superficial similarities with the Camma, the Ddraig lacks subspace drives or standard armament, instead functioning as a kamikaze drone. It targets any fighter or bomber that gets within range and chases it down, much like a missile. Unlike a traditional missile, Ddraigs are large, nearly the size of a torpedo, and much slower, but they have much longer flight times. Post-flight analysis suggests it uses an on-broad AI much like standard ADEIS drones, allowing it to chose and change targets, and pursue strikecraft for several minutes even at very long ranges.<br/><br/>The IF Ddraig has been observed flying in wings of 2 to 6, and so far only seen deployed by A.D.E.IS.01. Consider them Class C threats when allied point defenses are present, and Class B threats when encountered without turret support, or if allied bombers are present."
