1468, "(fr)The Stylet anti-subsystem bomb features a small electromagnetic pulse-based warhead in its tip, allowing for damage to be caused to enemy subsystems without significantly impacting the hull strength of capital ships. Relying on a tracking system identical to the MX-50 heatseeker, the Stylet's fire-and-forget nature has made it effective in swarming enemy turrets with large numbers of the missile, often carried on board Zeus or Athéna bombers. Attempts are currently being made to cross the subsystem-harming warhead of the Stylet with the long-range aspect lock of the Ballista to make a more effective anti-turret and anti-subsystem weapon."
