10661, "(fr)Also known as the STX-3478 Turing, the Locuste is a field-expedient refit of the Frelon swarm missile. The original ultraviolet tracking sensor has been wholly replaced with an LNA-designed subspace analytics package. The weapon is a gross violation of GTA guidelines on field modifications, but nevertheless seen as a pragmatic adaption to the developing strategic situation in Luyten.<br/><br/>The Locuste operates on the same principle as a 20th-century anti-radiation missile: rather than tracking ADEIS drones directly, it locks onto their subspace communication signatures. ADEIS craft send each other constant updates on their current and planned flight path through continuous, wide-brand subspace broadcasts, both tactically and on a strategic level. A team lead by Dr. Tsega Sarno cross-referenced LNA traffic analysis with data captured from the ICv Gallécie to come up with a partial $quotephrasebook$quote. By using ADEIS's own navigational data for terminal guidance, the otherwise sluggish GTM-4 has become unerringly accurate in all but the most extreme approach angles. This came at the cost of making the missile useless against other craft$semicolon however, the Locuste's multi-aspect capabilities, which allow it to independently track, intercept, and neutralize multiple drones in a single volley is unquestionably worth it.<br/><br/>Simply put, ADEIS itself tells the Locuste where to aim."
10660, "(fr)GTiM-4-R Locuste"
