1623, "(fr)The Harbinger was developed alongside the Ursa bomber, and both designs were intended to complement each other. The Harbinger is the largest fusion warhead ever created, and the first bomber-launched weapon intended to destroy enemy capital ships outright. Blast-shaping elements in the Harbinger's hull ensure that its detonation is focused as efficiently as possible, giving the weapon massive anti-subsystem power in addition to raw hull damage. Standard tactics call for light bombers to strip away a target's point defenses, followed by a Harbinger strike to neutralize the engines$semicolon however, the turbulence of fleet actions rarely makes things so simple, and heavy bomber squadrons have found success in firing their Harbingers at point-blank range, using their own shields to deny enemy defenses a clear shot at the bomb.<br/><br/>The addition of Vasudan engineers to Project Harbinger delayed its rollout, but resulted in a much more potent bomb. It is theorized that the Shivan Lucifer would have accomplished its objectives without this collaboration, although it is impossible to be sure. It is, however, uncontroversial that the Harbinger's compatibility with the PVN's Amon bomber was a deciding factor in key battles against the Shivan fleet."
