1102, "(fr)The Fury is an unguided rocket used throughout the GTA. With no guidance hardware, the Fury is extremely small, allowing even light fighters to carry many of them$semicolon this, along with the Fury's fast cycle rate, allows Fury-armed ships to deliver intense bursts of damage. Furies are typically employed as assault weapons aboard Apollon- and Hercule-class fighters, setting up quick strafing runs against transports, freighters, and even cruisers. Some interceptor pilots have reported success with the Fury as well, since a bomber's large size naturally compensates for the Fury's lack of guidance. The Fury also offers adequate shield and subsystem damage, although hitting turrets with it requires pilots to get into close range.<br/><br/>The Fury remains an effective weapon, but is somewhat outshone by newer systems, especially the Frelon swarm missile. The Alliance has some interest in a replacement weapon that retains the Fury's positive qualities in a modernized package."
