10636, "(fr)The Lancette is a an anti-subsystem and anti-shield gun fielded by the paramilitary Second Dawn Society. The Lancette fills a similar tactical niche as the Disruptor, but its operating principles are entirely different. The Lancette fires a stream of electrically conductive plasma, destructively linking impacted shields with the firing ship's reactor. This design has also proven highly effective against fighter shields, granting a degree of tactical flexibility. The Lancette's main feature, however, is an array of electromagnetic guidance rings at the weapon's muzzle. These rings coordinate with the firing ship's targeting computer to direct the plasma stream as it exits the barrel. This $quoteaim assist$quote function allows the Lancette to effectively disable small craft with relative ease.<br/><br/>While effective in the hands of a trained pilot, the Lancette suffers from an exorbitant per-unit cost, as well as a number of technical issues. Sustained fire can overwhelm the mechanical tolerances of the aim assist system, leading to a failure mode which the weapon's designer describes as $quotefiring wildly in random directions$quote. When approached by LNA weapons researchers, this same engineer indicated that they'd $quotecompletely given up on solving that$quote, and that $quoteunless you know of a lubricant that can survive a plasma storm and costs less than a cruiser per liter, I'm done with that thing$quote. This attitude is not shared by the larger Second Dawn Society, however$semicolon given the organization's belief in an inevitable second Great War, the utility the weapon would offer in capture operations against Shivan targets compels the organization to continue their research.<br/><br/>While the technical challenges of aim assist are well-known, building the technology into a subsystem disruptor is a creative solution to some of them. Firing the weapon in short bursts is often enough to destroy a subsystem or pierce a shield quadrant without triggering the $quotewild firing$quote issue, and pilots carrying the Lancette are advised to adopt such a firing pattern as a matter of habit. The SDA' stockpile of Lancets is vanishingly small, and they are loathe to part with them, so they may only be loaded out with the authorization of a squadron leader."
10635, "(fr)Tactical Disruptor and shield-breaker,
Experimental aim assist,
Fire in short bursts"
10634, "(fr)SDSg-14 Lancette"
10633, "(fr)Lancette"
10632, "(fr)Shield Capacitor"
10631, "(fr)The Shield Pack was developed by the Luyten New Alliance to facilitate operations within the highly energetic Doceitov anomaly. Adapted from the miniature shield projector carried by Stylet missiles, the Shield Pack is capable of emitting a short-lived, high-intensity pulse which rapidly re-energizes the shields of the firing ship. The LNA designed the Shield Pack both for their own use and for sale to the GTA, and is designed to be compatible with capacitors taking from the defunct ML-16 weapon. The Shield Pack's prototypical status carries some technical limitations, such as the inability to recharge the system without the aid of a support ship."
10630, "(fr)2-Second Shield Overcharge,
Call Support To Reload"
10714, "(fr)Shield Pack"
10629, "(fr)The Magnetic Grapple is a common civilian tool typically mounted on shuttles and transports at spaceborne dockyards. The grapple utilizes a resonant magnetic field to effectively latch onto an object at distance, allowing it to be slowly and carefully manipulated by the ship or drone equipped with it. These devices are most commonly used by utility ships in large cargo depots, where they allow for the repositioning of cargo containers without the logistical expenses of spinning up a freighter."
10628, "(fr)50hw Magnetic Grapple"
10627, "(fr)Mag Grapple"
1079, "(fr)The Force-CXI is a launcher system for the CXI series of tracking devices. The CXI bug has the ability to record information from enemy communication systems, and automatically links with GTA communication platforms to allow for remote tracking of a tagged ship through multiple systems. The Force-CXI was originally designed by GTI for special operations use, but has become a common sight among customs enforcement units, who use it to ensure suspect ships cannot easily escape into subspace."
1487, "(fr)The Barracuda torpedo is the oldest weapon still in mainline use with the Parliamentary Vasudan Navy, having been in their inventories since the start of the Terran-Vasudan War over fifteen years ago. The Barracuda is a small-scale nuclear weapon, capable of causing significant harm to cruisers and stationary objects. Vasudan engineers have modified most Barracudas to be capable of firing both in an aspect-seeking and in a dumbfire role, allowing for flexibility heavier ordnance does not have. The Barracuda is the lightest anti-warship weapon in service, and even mainline PVN squadrons often carry the jointly designed Tsunami instead."
1078, "(fr)Tracking Beacon, Extremely Low Damage"
1077, "(fr)Force-CXI Target Acquisition"
1075, "(fr)With stocks of argon depleting for use in the various Prometheus variants in service, GTA engineers have been forced to improvise new means to maintain the otherwise useless weapons. By replacing the argon injector of the Prometheus with an EM modulator derived from the Banshee, the Prometheus R was created, allowing for older weapons to be retrofitted to working order. Due to its experimental design, the Prometheus R is somewhat temperamental. While it boasts slightly higher hull damage than the HL-7, some pilots prefer to use the HL-7 even in assault roles for its flexibility."
10626, "(fr)Anti-Hull Weapon, EMP Effect Disorients Targets"
1074, "(fr)GTW-5R Prometheus Retrofit"
1073, "(fr)Prometheus R"
1072, "(fr)The Akheton Corporation's entry into the SDG market is a Vasudan upgrade of the GTW-41a. Intended to be even more effective than its predecessor, the Akheton SDG is compatible with both Terran and Vasudan fighters, and is significantly cheaper to produce than the Disruptor. It is expected that the Akheton SDG will become the standard subsystem destroyer for the foreseeable future."
1069, "(fr)PVW Akheton SDG"
1068, "(fr)Akheton SDG"
1066, "(fr)The Mekhu HL-7 is a derivative of the Terran-created Subach HL-7. The Mekhu applies Vasudan combat philosophy to the original design, having less individual damage per bolt but a notably higher rate of fire when compared to the Subach. Like the Subach, the Mekhu has been well accepted by Vasudan pilots, particularly when utilized in the quad bank of Thot or Taouret fighters where its full rate of fire can be put to effective use against Hammer of Light renegades."
1065, "(fr)Vasudan HL-7,
High Fire Rate,
Slightly Less Damage"
1064, "(fr)PVW Mekhu HL-7"
1063, "(fr)Mekhu HL-7"
10625, "(fr)Subach HL-7"
1062, "(fr)Subach-Innes' HL-7 is intended as a successor to the Avenger. The weapon uses the same fundamental paradigm of a physical core encased in excited plasma, and this hybrid approach has once again demonstrated exceptional energy efficiency. The Subach HL-7 differs primarily in its excitement mechanism: a ring of highly focused xasers surrounding the primary emitter. The HL-7's per-unit cost has been criticized as excessive, and its internal heat sinks have shown themselves to be somewhat lacking, creating a maintenance hassle. Nevertheless, the HL-7's combination of a high rate of fire, good effect against both hulls and shields, and efficiency have made it an instant favorite with Fleet pilots. As the Avenger struggles to keep up with modern shields and Prometheus stocks decline, the HL-7 has been pushed into the role of a standard-issue primary weapon."
10624, "(fr)High Hull/Average Shield Damage, Low Power Draw"
1061, "(fr)GTW Subach HL-7"
1060, "(fr)Subach HL-7"
1059, "(fr)The Leech Cannon utilizes a self-destructive plasma burst to act as a miniature split-second capacitor, draining the energy of enemy afterburners, shields, and energy weapons. In practice, however, it has been disliked for its inability to cause any serious form of harm to enemy ships. Early stages of development are underway to replace the Leech with a more effective weapon capable of performing the same duties."
1058, "(fr)Tactical Weapon, Drains Energy, Low Damage"
1057, "(fr)GTW-43 Leech Cannon"
1056, "(fr)Leech Cannon"
1055, "(fr)Designed as a special-issue upgrade to the standard Prometheus, the Prometheus A was used extensively by both rebel and loyalist GTI forces during the Hades Rebellion. This variant offered even higher damage than the original at the expense of slightly increased power draw. Much like the original Prometheus, the Prometheus A has become vanishingly rare after the collapse of the Sol jump node."
1054, "(fr)GTW-5A Prometheus Advanced"
1053, "(fr)Prometheus A"
1052, "(fr)The Prometheus was based around advanced argon laser technology, utilizing a fully out-of-phase projectile system to engage enemy targets. While slightly less effective against shielding than the Avenger, it was much more capable against enemy ship hulls, and thus became the weapon of choice against the more durable but less thickly shielded ships of Terran criminals and Hammer of Light renegades. The Prometheus became a workhorse weapon during the Shivan Incursion. However, the loss of the Sol jump node cut off access to Earth's supply of argon, cutting Prometheus production virtually to nil."
1051, "(fr)Hull-Attack Weapon,
Average Shield Damage"
1050, "(fr)Prometheus"
1049, "(fr)The Shield Breaker, commonly referred to as the S-Breaker, is a prototype weapon developed by GTI. The S-Breaker is an electromagnetic weapon much like the Banshee, but it is highly modulated, linking with the sensors of the firing craft to calculate an optimal anti-frequency for disrupting the target’s shields. This has a downside, however, as the Shield Breaker is physically incapable of harming enemy subsystems or hulls. The S-Breaker has proven effective in concert with a hull-penetrating weapon such as the Prometheus R. It also boasts an unusually long range, making for an effective initiation weapon."
1048, "(fr)Long-Range Shield Breaker, No Hull Damage"
1047, "(fr)GTW-99 Shield Breaker"
1046, "(fr)S-Breaker"
10623, "(fr)The Railgun Evo is a development of the GTW Railgun prototype weapon that was developed by Galactic Terran Intelligence before and during the Hades Rebellion. Though the GTA abandoned the Railgun as too slow and unwieldy for conventional combat, the Second Dawn Society later revisited the concept. The Railgun Evo functions in a conceptually equivalent manner, but adds auxiliary gauss coils around the rails for better guidance, and a sabot made of newly-developed collapsed-core molybdenum. Though the sabot's increased density allows it to damage hulls notably better than the original Railgun, unstable molecular bonding make it even less effective against energy shielding than the original."
10621, "(fr)GTW-65d Railgun Evo"
10620, "(fr)Railgun Evo"
1045, "(fr)A GTI prototype cannon, the Railgun was originally developed as an attempt to penetrate the shields of the Lucifer superdestroyer. The weapon uses a series of electromagnets firing with millisecond precision to accelerate caseless uranium slugs at extreme velocity. While its range, accuracy, and impact force are the highest in the Terran arsenal, it has proven ineffective in its intended anti-shield role. The weapon also suffers from an extended recharge cycle. Although the Railgun is technically a ballistic weapon, the slugs are extremely small, and for tactical purposes the quantity of ammunition is unlimited."
1044, "(fr)Long-Range Anti-Hull Weapon, Long Recharge Cycle"
1043, "(fr)GTW-65 Railgun"
1042, "(fr)Railgun"
10619, "(fr)Banshee"
10618, "(fr)Banshee"
1041, "(fr)Developed by Galactic Terran Intelligence well before their betrayal of the GTA, the Banshee is a plasma-vectored electromagnetic pulse weapon. The Banshee’s rapid pulses of exceptionally strong electromagnetic energy were intended to quickly chew apart the shields of Shivan ships, which had limited hull strength and shielding far more capable than Terran or Vasudan fighters. The weapon's name comes from the sonic disturbance reported by pilots firing the weapon. While the Banshee is effective in its role, its high cost combined the disappearance of the Shivans from known space has resulted in it becoming limited issue, though the concepts it introduced will likely see use in future weapon designs.<br/><br/>Like the Avenger, the Banshee has a turret variant, typically mounted on Ursa and Amon strategic bombers."
1040, "(fr)EM Weapon, High Power Draw, Extreme Shield Damage"
1039, "(fr)GTW-7 Banshee"
1038, "(fr)Banshee"
1037, "(fr)The GTW-32 Flail is a rapid-fire, low-energy weapon originally developed from scientific equipment. The Flail was intended to disrupt Shivan shields and inflicts very little hull damage$semicolon however, it has shown itself to be unexpectedly effective as a kinetic weapon, knocking enemy strikecraft off their intended course and making them vulnerable to a follow-up attack. Sustained Flail fire can even $quotepin$quote less maneuverable fighters and bombers. Some pilots have also had experience using the Flail as a bomb intercept weapon, leveraging its high rate of fire to prematurely detonate enemy warheads."
1036, "(fr)Low Power Draw,
Kinetic Effect,
Moderate Shield Damage"
