11371, "(fr)The DIRCM BriteBurst is a cost-effective but unsophisticated countermeasure rarely encountered in the GTA but common in the civilian world. Unlike the sophisticated electronics of other modern countermeasures, the BriteBurst employs extreme heat to break missile lock. While of limited effect against aspect-seeking missiles, these countermeasures are highly effective against the heat-seeking ordnance typically employed by, and against, private security forces.<br/><br/>LOCAL ADDENDUM: Post-flight review of guncam footage collected during the Carter engagement indicates that the BriteBurst is unusually effective against the raider's shield-breaker missiles. Our working theory is that the BriteBurst's long active phase interacts favorably with the shield-breaker's long flight time. Because of this the flare should be launched early while the missile is still in cruising flight. Security contractor Makarov has made his wing's supply of BriteBurst's available to any pilot wishing to use them."
